description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

event_name: Our Famous 90s vs 00s Summer Boat Cruise!
description: The Fox Cabaret presents the fifth edition of our famous 90s vs 00s party…on a BOAT! This is always SUCH a fun time and a very special experience that highlights the best of Vancouver <3 Featuring the always stellar Common People DJs Adam & Bryan! About 90s vs 00s Night TLC or The Black Eyed Peas? Ginuwine or 50 Cent? Madonna or Gaga? House of Pain or Outkast? Whether you're into Electric Circus or TRL we've got all the hits, gems, and anthems of the funnest decades. Which decade will reign supreme? Come dance the night away + decide for your self! Aboard the MV Abitibi Plaza of Nations Marina 750 Pacific Blvd Dock B (Located directly behind the Edgewater Casino) Your ticket gets you into the party at The Fox Cabaret afterwards for free (dependant on capacity) to keep the party going until 2am! Boarding 7:00 pm Departing 8:00 pm Docking 11:00 pm 19+ Refunds are available 7 days or more before the event - no exceptions.
location: Plaza of Nations Marina 750 Pacific Blvd Vancouver, BC V6B 5E7

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha Cha - Intermediate/ Advanced
description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

description: Come join BC Swing Victoria for our second fabulous (and FREE) evening of fun and West Coast Swing dancing at Centennial Square! The schedule for the night will be: 6pm (sharp) there will be an intro lesson to West Coast Swing. 7 - 9pm WCS music will be provided by DJ Carolyn Gebbie. Note: For those who are familiar with the 2019 WCS Rally routine, and would like to practice performing it live prior to Sept 7, the 'Hands Up” song will be played at 7:30 and 8:30pm. There will be WCS instructors on hand to answer questions about WCS or how to improve your WCS dancing.
location: Centennial Square, Victoria, British Columbia, Canada

description: Embrace the moment. Enrich YOUR Life! Give yourself an hour of sound healing. Maggie plays the handmade Tibetan bowls guiding the group into a Chakra balancing meditation to open with Susannah offering song and sound of singing in spiritual bliss. Ali plays violin waving us together in oneness. Master Maggie has worked with spiritual masters the Dhai Lama, Eckhart Tolle and Mooji, trained as a nun-monk she embraces body and mind wellness. Susannah breathes song and sound of inspirational improvisation frequencies. As Ali's violin sounds wave us into oneness. Book Now (limited space) at Copper Mountain 250-382-3469 coppermountain@shawbiz.ca
location: 225 Menzies ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8V2G6, CA

description: Come dance by the beach! I'll bring a speaker and some music. The ground has a bit of loose sand/dust so I recommend some close toed shoes; but that makes it so that you can wear regular shoes and do turns and pivot on one foot without hurting your knees or ankles! The cool sea breeze helps keep the heat of the day at bay but as the sun sets it might get a bit cool so bring a sweater or light jacket if you get cold. If you aren't sure what fusion is but want to dip into it or into social partner dancing come on out and I'll give you a quick crash course to get you dancing in no time (probably about 5 minutes).
location: Cadboro-Gyro Park, 2625 Sinclair Rd, Victoria, British Columbia

event_name: Texture Your Moves for West Coast Swing
description: We will guide you through practical musicality and movement drills that will 'colour in' any pattern in your repertoire. You'll learn: +++ How you can do more styling without feeling inhibited OR being reckless. +++ How to preserve your partnership connection while still expressing yourself. +++ How to enjoy being musical even with partners who are missing skills. +++ How to respect the rules of the WCS while learning to bend them. This workshop is for you if; You have no idea how to dance differently to different genres of music, so most of your dances look or feel the same. You feel like you are just walking through patterns without any real character to your movement and you feel robotic and stiff.
location: 516 Quadra St, Victoria, BC V8V 3S3, Canada
price: $30 via etransfer (for 2hr workshop) $40 (if paying at the door.)

About FOM Music Society: We are a registered charitable organization that offers music programs in support of mental health. No referral necessary! Our regular programs run from Sept-June, and most are continuous entry.  We offer a huge range of group music lessons, performance groups, community concerts, and special events. Come make music with us! To become a member or get more info, please visit our website: www.friendsofmusic.ca
location: Eric Martin Pavilion Theatre, Victoria, British Columbia

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

event_name: Slow Balboa Weekend - SAVE THE DATE!
description: Join us for a weekend of learning Slow Balboa with Lizou and Eloise! Slow Bal, or Slow Balboa, is a close embrace swing dance from the 1940s. You dance it to the slow jazz music of that time. It is a playful and above all elegant dance, influenced by historic dancers Dean and Nancy Raftery and Ray Cunningham. The event includes 4 hours of Slow Balboa classes on Saturday daytime, a Social Dance with DJ Lizou on Saturday evening, and 2 hours of Slow Balboa classes + 2 hours of Open Practice/ Tea Dance on Sunday daytime.
location: 500 Campbell AVE, VANCOUVER, BC, V6A3K1, CA

event_name: Mix & Match competition and DJ Nomad at Rhythm City Strut
description: Introducing free, fierce and friendly monthly competitions at Strut! No need to register in advance, no competition fees: just show up at the dance, and step forward when we call for competitors! It's a fun way to challenge yourself, show off what you've been working on, and explore new partnerships. We start with a classic Mix & Match competition. What is a Mix & Match? Simply sign up as a lead or a follow and you'll get randomly paired with dancers of the other role. It's mostly about having fun and doing your best with your partner and the music! This week your DJ is DJ Nomad (Lawrence Chan), with comps music from DJ Monsieur O (Jean-Michel Oblette).

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Free Outdoor Intro Dance Class + Social | Summer Series
description: Join us for an introduction to Kizomba with Aaron and Fernanda— part of our summer series, proudly sponsored by the City of Victoria! Every Monday | June–August 5:30–7:30 PM 1.5-hour dance class followed by a 30-minute outdoor social Dance style rotates monthly — check our content calendar on our website for full details! This free outdoor event is open to everyone — no partner or dance experience needed. All ages, bodies, and abilities are warmly welcomed! Whether you’re dancing the night away or soaking in the summer vibes, come be part of this vibrant community celebration. Don’t forget to bring a water bottle and come ready to move!
location: Ship's Point Inner Harbour, Big Blue Sailing, Victoria, BC V8W, Canada

description: Get ready for the most fun you can have on (and off) two wheels! Join us for Ignition Track Days! Aprilia will be on-site with demo bikes for you to test. Whether you're a seasoned track rider or just starting out, this is your chance to experience Italian performance at its finest. Albi’s legendary Gelato Truck will be back, keeping the paddock cool and the energy high! New to the track? No problem. Our crew and community are all about helping each other out, sharing tips, and making sure everyone feels welcome. Come solo or with friends—you’ll leave with more than just lap times. You’ll leave with memories, laughs, and a whole new crew. Limited spots available—book now to secure your place!

description: Book your spot, and ride your motorcycle on the beautiful Vancouver Island Motorsports Circuit (VIMC) just outside Duncan, BC. Track is HOTT from 9AM to 12PM and again from 1PM to 4PM. Higgy's does 20 minute sessions or about 120 minutes of seat time. We focus on Safety, Fun, and Good Vibes! Several of our Control Riders are professional Motorcycle Instructors and they are happy to help you improve your riding throughout the day, at no cost to you!

We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson

Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha Cha - Intermediate/ Advanced
description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Welcome to our monthly Wednesday evening Dance Temple! Conscious dance and community connection in sacred space. A monthly offering on the last Wednesdays of the month, with the same format as Sunday mornings. Join us at Edelweiss Club for an ecstatic dance journey on Wednesday, May 28th. Featuring Jennifer Eve (aka Poetic) as our guest facilitator/dj! Details for Wednesday, May 28th: Facilitation and music set by Jennifer Eve Bio: Jennifer Eve, aka Poetic, combines her savvy ear for music, her warrior poet spirit, and her dancing raver heart, to skillfully kindle soulful journeys that ignite dance floors everywhere.

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.

description: SpoKizomba is a cozy, all-in-one retreat for Kizomba lovers taking place in Spokane, Washington from August 15–17, 2025. Join us for hands-on workshops with instructor Ashby Laine focused on Kizomba technique, musicality, and embodiment. Three social dances featuring Kizomba, Semba, Zouk, Ghetto Zouk, and more, with music by DJ Kalcidony and DJ Mario. Special excursions thoughtfully planned for summertime fun and great community vibes. Wellness activities and excursions to help you rest and recharge. Shared meals from Friday dinner through Sunday lunch. Optional onsite lodging to keep things as simple as possible. SpoKizomba is small by design (capped at about 60 dancers), so it stays personal and facilitates real connection. Whether you’re new to Kizomba or have been putting down roots in this scene for a while now, we’re certain this will be a weekend well spent. Come on over—the fam’s all here! TICKET OPTIONS & PRICING Tier 1 | Earliest Bird: $245 (Only 10 tickets available, closes June 1) Tier 2 | Early Bird: $260 (Only 12 tickets available, closes July 1) Tier 3 | Full Price: $285 Get your ticket here: givebutter.com/SpoKizomba-2025 Note: We can’t accommodate refunds, but we’ll happily help coordinate transfers at no charge. Just let us know how we can help! For more FAQs and details, visit: spokanekizombafamily.com/spokizomba-2025 .

description: Blues and Lindy Dance featuring all the usual suspects and special guests. Nothing else like it. The Swing Out: Jazz AND Dusty Blues Edition! Slow Drag and Traditional Blues and Swing Dance 7-10 dance featuring a line up of the Swing Out Super Stars~!!! All styles of dance and partner dance are welcome. Also you do not have to dance to come out; this Speakeasy is a great place to enjoy something from the bar and enjoy the cabaret. This month only From 6-7 there is a FREE HOUR LONG DROP IN Lindy Lesson available for FREE for anyone with a ticket to the dance!! The venue can be hard to find - It's in the Artiste Building at 2050 Scotia Street, but you must enter through the glass door by the loading bay at the back of the building. See the pin on our website for the location, and don't give up you will find it! The Swing Out is a safe and welcoming space for people from all backgrounds including the BIPOC and 2SLGBTQIA+ communities. Consent is always a must on the dancefloor. We respectfully acknowledge that this event is held on the unceded homelands of the xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam), Skwxwú7mesh (Squamish), and səl̓ílwətaʔɬ (Tsleil-Waututh) First Nations.
location: The Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret, 2050 Scotia Street Vancouver, BC V5T 4T1

description: This 3 day event will be in one of Western Canada's prettiest and artsiest small towns. Registration is by individual or pair, no partner required. However, we will strive for role balance at this event, so we recommend signing up with a partner. The intention for this event is to create a fabulous series of Milongas, with generous food and drink offerings, and a warm atmosphere of mutual inclusion and respect. We seek to honor the codigos and traditions of Argentine Tango and to create an atmosphere of camaraderie and togetherness. All Tango styles are welcome as long as good floorcraft and consideration for others is maintained. So looking forward to sharing our little town and big hearts with you! We have a lot of great moments mapped out for you on this weekend, Prize draws, group meals, parties, and some fun ice-breaker activities during registration times before the opening Milonga on Friday and throughout the weekend Passes and more info: www.nelsonbctango.com.
location: 703 Stromme LANE, NELSON, BC, V1L6H7, CA

description: Jazz, Blues and the sweet notes in between Maureen Washington is the Winner of the 2014 Black Canadian Award for Best Jazz and Soul Artist! A consummate performer, she slips easily from sassy to sexy within a single line of lyrics, at times echoing the haunting tones of Etta James and Carmen McRae, then faster than the mind and ear can make the transition, Maureen Washington exudes the impish irreverence of Jann Arden and the vocal agility of Holly Cole. With all splendor attached to such comparisons, Maureen’s musical style remains distinctly her own. Her vocal diversity lends itself to performances of blues, swing jazz and funk , and her versatile repertoire, ranges from classics to lively originals. It's been a while since we've presented Maureen, her shows are usually sold out, so make sure to get your tickets in advance!
location: Upstairs Lounge, Oak Bay Recreation Centre, 1975 Bee Street, Oak Bay, BC V8R 5E6
